                </head>
                <para>
                    <bop/>
                    <bos/>
                    <paratext>This book would not exist but for the support and assistance received from many sources.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>As always, my family has been supportive and encouraging.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>My friends have excused my occasional preoccupation with reading Panel decisions and
                        writing up these developments.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>I continue to be indebted to my law partners and my law firm, Maslon, LLP, for their
                        support, advice, and assistance.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>Our clients have provided the wonderful and rich education in complex litigation in many
                        state and federal courts.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>I am honored to be able to help solve the litigation problems they have faced.
                        <eos/>
                    </paratext>
                    <eop/>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <bop/>
                    <bos/>
                    <paratext>Lynnette Shanahan, Patricia Porter, and Dixie Rud have provided able assistance in putting
                        these materials on paper.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>As always, I also appreciate the sacrifices and forbearances of my family.
                        <eos/>
                    </paratext>
                    <eop/>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <bop/>
                    <bos/>
                    <paratext>The Panel Clerk&apos;s office has been a tremendous resource for making this book more
                        useful to those who practice before the Panel.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>The Clerk of the Panel, Jeffery N. Lüthi, continues in the fine tradition of the office,
                        and has shared useful insights into the work of the Panel.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>The former Clerk of the Panel, Michael J. Beck, provided invaluable assistance and
                        guidance in the preparation of this book.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>This assistance is typical of that offered to all litigants with matters before the Panel.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>It is especially appreciated by this author.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>Patricia Howard, who served from the Panel&apos;s inception until early 1999, was
                        similarly helpful.
                        <eos/>
                    </paratext>
                    <eop/>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <bop/>
                    <bos/>
                    <paratext>It should go without saying, but any errors that remain are my sole responsibility.
                        <eos/>
                        <bos/>If you find one, please let me know so I can fix it.
                        <eos/>
                    </paratext>
                    <eop/>
                </para>
